# Adoption-candidate suppressions for `setup.sh --check`.
#
# Lists patterns of ~/.claude/{skills,agents,hooks}/* entries that should NOT
# be flagged as candidates for adoption into the claude stow package.
# One pattern per line; supports bash globs. Lines starting with # are comments.
#
# Examples:
#   skills/gsd-*           # ignore everything from the GSD plugin
#   agents/gsd-*.md        # ignore all GSD agents
#   skills/some-thing      # exact match
#
# To dismiss something later: append a pattern that matches it and rerun --check.
# To adopt something: mv it into the package + restow (then it stops being a candidate).

# --- Baseline: everything present when this file was first generated ---
